2026-05-11T06:24Z verify_shipped POST /trades idempotency UX gap: re-POSTs return HTTP 200 with byte-identical body — NO `inserted` flag, NO `already_recorded` indicator. Agent cannot distinguish first-write from idempotent re-read. The verifier internally tracks `insertRes.inserted` boolean but the route handler strips it via `NextResponse.json(result.row, {status: 200})`. Operationally important for: (a) UI differentiation first-submit vs retry, (b) metrics avoiding double-count "newly verified", (c) cross-source dedup observability (cron beat agent-submit). Fix shape proposed: ~1-line change to surface `{...result.row, inserted: result.inserted}`. Awaiting operator decision on whether to file as follow-up on #738 or inline pre-merge.
